sition(path string) (int, error)`** — Count JSONL lines. Same logic as Claude Code's implementation since both use JSONL. Use `bufio.Reader` + `ReadBytes('\\\\n')` to handle arbitrarily long lines.\\n\\n- **`ExtractPrompts(sessionRef string, fromOffset int) ([]string, error)`** — Reuse `transcript.ParseFromFileAtLine()` + `transcript.ExtractUserContent()` + `textutil.StripIDEContextTags()`. Identical to Claude Code's implementation since the shared transcript package already normalizes `role` → `type` and strips `<user_query>` tags.\\n\\n- **`ExtractSummary(sessionRef string) (string, error)`** — Reuse `transcript.ParseFromBytes()`, walk backward to find last assistant text block. Identical to Claude Code's implementation.\\n\\n- **`ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path string, startOffset int) ([]string, int, error)`** — Return an error: `(nil, 0, ErrNoToolUseBlocks)`. Cursor transcripts don't contain `tool_use` blocks, so file extraction is not supported. Returning an error (rather than nil files) makes the intent explicit: \\\"can't extract\\\" vs \\\"found nothing.\\\" All 3 call sites handle errors gracefully — they print a warning and fall through to git-status-based detection. Define a package-level sentinel: `var ErrNoToolUseBlocks = errors.New(\\\"cursor transcripts do not contain tool_use blocks; file detection uses git status\\\")`.\\n\\n### 2. Remove \\\"does NOT implement\\\" comment\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go` (line 47-49)\\n\\nRemove the comment block:\\n```go\\n// Note: CursorAgent does NOT implement TranscriptAnalyzer. Cursor's transcript\\n// format does not contain tool_use blocks that would allow extracting modified\\n// files. File detection relies on git status instead.\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Remove \\\"ModifiedFiles left empty\\\" comment\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go` (lines 106-107)\\n\\nUpdate the `ReadSession` comment from:\\n```go\\n// Note: ModifiedFiles is left empty because Cursor's transcript format does not\\n// contain tool_use blocks. File detection relies on git status instead.\\n```\\nTo:\\n```go\\n// Note: ModifiedFiles is left empty because Cursor's transcript does not contain\\n// tool_use blocks for file detection. TranscriptAnalyzer extracts prompts and\\n// summaries; file detection relies on git status.\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Add tests\\n\\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/transcript_test.go`\\n\\nTests using `sampleTranscriptLines()` (already defined in `cursor_test.go`):\\n\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_GetTranscriptPosition`** — Write sample transcript, verify line count = 4\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_GetTranscriptPosition_EmptyPath`** — Empty path returns 0\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_GetTranscriptPosition_NonexistentFile`** — Returns 0, nil\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractPrompts`** — Verify 2 prompts extracted, `<user_query>` tags stripped\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractPrompts_WithOffset`** — fromOffset=2, only second prompt returned\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractPrompts_EmptyFile`** — Returns empty slice\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractSummary`** — Returns last assistant message text\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractSummary_EmptyFile`** — Returns empty string\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`** — Returns nil files, correct position (4)\\n- **`TestCursorAgent_ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset_EmptyPath`** — Returns 0\\n- **Compile-time interface check:** `var _ agent.TranscriptAnalyzer = (*CursorAgent)(nil)`\\n\\n### 5. Add compile-time interface check\\n\\nIn `transcript.go`, add:\\n```go\\nvar _ agent.TranscriptAnalyzer = (*CursorAgent)(nil)\\n```\\n\\n## Key reuse points\\n\\n- `transcript.ParseFromFileAtLine()` — shared JSONL parser with `role` → `type` normalization (`cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go`)\\n- `transcript.ParseFromBytes()` — shared byte-level parser (`cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go`)\\n- `transcript.ExtractUserContent()` — extracts user content from raw message (`cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go`)\\n- `tex